00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 17=

19
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:39,960
Why did you pick a fight with him?

20
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:42,240
What if you actually hurt the old man?

21
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,080
So what if he's old?

22
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:44,910
He can't just act entitled like that.

23
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:46,750
He criticizes everyone he sees,

24
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,030
saying no one is good enough,

25
00:01:48,190 --> 00:01:50,030
as if only those four can perform,

26
00:01:50,030 --> 00:01:51,476
and the rest of us are just shouting.

27
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:54,030
They just know some traditional opera.

28
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,920
Ask them to sing Hong Deng Ji.

29
00:01:56,230 --> 00:01:57,390
Ask them to sing Sha Jia Bang.

30
00:01:57,390 --> 00:01:58,650
See if they can even do it.

31
00:01:58,661 --> 00:01:59,550
What's wrong with you?

32
00:01:59,550 --> 00:02:00,390
Why hassle over this?

33
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:03,830
Your drumming does have some issues.

34
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:05,030
We have a better one.

35
00:02:05,550 --> 00:02:07,000
He's locked up in prison now.

36
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,320
Why not get him out?

37
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,200
Can't you be more open-minded?

38
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:12,840
Can't you be more generous?

39
00:02:13,070 --> 00:02:13,910
What do you mean?

40
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:16,280
Go and apologize to him.

41
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:18,070
Why should I?

42
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,280
It's already enough

43
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,430
that I didn't go after Zhou,

44
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:22,750
and now I have to apologize?

45
00:02:23,030 --> 00:02:23,960
Deputy Troupe Leader,

46
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,470
this isn't over. I'm telling you.

47
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,030
It's not over?

48
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:28,280
Those four old men

49
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:30,070
have already got one foot in the grave.

50
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:32,960
Just give them a way out.

51
00:02:33,790 --> 00:02:35,200
We still have to rehearse the play.

52
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,430
Not a chance. Take it or leave it.

53
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:40,000
He Dachui, think of the big picture.

54
00:02:40,350 --> 00:02:41,230
Do it for me.

55
00:02:41,230 --> 00:02:42,640
Forget it. I'm not doing it.

56
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:46,950
He Dachui is a Party member after all.

57
00:02:46,950 --> 00:02:48,790
He's the trainee class teacher

58
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:50,400
and a model worker every year.

59
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:54,280
But those old losers broke his bones.

60
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,280
This behavior is extremely vile.

61
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,920
They must be punished, Troupe Leader.

62
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,120
The key is

63
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,920
that it has caused public outrage.

64
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,560
If unpunished,
He Dachui won't let it go.

65
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,590
Nor will the orchestra,

66
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:12,480
the whole trainee class,

67
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,590
or the masses

68
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:14,920
of the troupe.

69
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:17,200
Your wife won't let it go either, right?

70
00:03:18,950 --> 00:03:20,150
My wife is also very angry.

71
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:26,200
What is going on here?

72
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:28,760
What's going on?

73
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:31,430
My wife is mad at me again.

74
00:03:32,870 --> 00:03:34,480
What's the reason this time?

75
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:36,590
Because of your wife. Why else?

76
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:39,310
Your wife wants
to play Lin Chong's wife.

77
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,400
She went to my wife and told her

78
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:44,240
Mi Lan was the one
who seduced me back then.

79
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,590
Now, she's digging up the past again.

80
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:48,430
I didn't even know about this.

81
00:03:49,310 --> 00:03:51,960
Luckily, she just hurt me to get a part.

82
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:54,080
If she wanted to be the troupe leader,

83
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,590
she probably would have killed me.

84
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,120
Master,

85
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,560
here, the brazier is ready.

86
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,430
Warm yourself up.

87
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:02,470
It's freezing.

88
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,120
Situan,

89
00:04:10,430 --> 00:04:11,520
pack your things.

90
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:14,000
Go back tomorrow. Don't follow me.

91
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:21,710
Is it because Dachui hated your act?

92
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,240
Master,

93
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,840
who'll take your robe if I leave?

94
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:34,120
I'll stop shaking the robe, okay?

95
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:41,470
He Dachui actually did a good thing.

96
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,190
His slap

97
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,240
didn't just knock your tooth out,

98
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:48,030
but cured your lifelong bad habits.

99
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,200
Master,

100
00:05:01,150 --> 00:05:02,240
don't make me leave.

101
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:09,400
Master, I'm begging you, Master.

102
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:21,750
Master.

103
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:25,470
Master.

104
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,270
Master!

105
00:05:33,220 --> 00:05:36,780
(Plead guilty and accept the law
Submit to management and reform)

106
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:43,270
Hu Sanyuan.

107
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:44,360
Hu Sanyuan,

108
00:05:44,590 --> 00:05:46,000
stop banging. You're so loud.

109
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:50,280
Do you know why I can't sew straight?

110
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:51,470
Why?

111
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:53,560
My right hand is messed up.

112
00:05:57,950 --> 00:05:59,920
I think your brain is messed up.

113
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,120
You're crazy.

114
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:03,430
Your hand won't obey you,

115
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:05,000
but it works fine for that bowl?

116
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:07,950
Stop it, will you?

117
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,430
Just stop it.

118
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,560
If you're crazy, knock your noggin.
Do you hear me?

119
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:20,070
Didn't you want to knock?

120
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,080
Come on.

121
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:23,870
Knock right here.

122
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,506
This is the root of his illness.

123
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,510
Won't this ruin me?

124
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:28,350
It won't.

125
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,640
Knock.

126
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,200
Wait a sec.

127
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:32,800
Gently, be gentle.

128
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:37,390
It won't work if you go light.

129
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:39,040
Knock harder.

130
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:41,600
The faster, the better.

131
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,560
Hu Sanyuan.

132
00:06:59,070 --> 00:06:59,910
Are you asleep?

133
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,160
Stop pretending to sleep.

134
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:10,030
What's on your mind?

135
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,390
Nothing.

136
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,070
Missing the outside?

137
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:23,310
How many days have you been in here?

138
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,720
1,750 days.

139
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:34,900
The fewer days you have left,

140
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,360
the more each one drags.

141
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:41,310
I actually think time's flying.

142
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:43,360
Come on, that's nonsense.

143
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,240
I'm telling you.

144
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:47,510
People who count down every day

145
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:49,630
never feel that time is flying.

146
00:07:51,870 --> 00:07:53,510
But to someone like me,

147
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,070
who doesn't count at all,

148
00:07:56,070 --> 00:07:57,160
every day feels the same.

149
00:08:07,950 --> 00:08:08,790
Veterinarian.

150
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,630
My back's burning.

151
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:13,800
Check it. It must be all bruised.

152
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,120
Burning means it's working.

153
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,920
This tapping is like Gua Sha

154
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,800
or Cupping.

155
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,630
It invigorates blood.

156
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,390
Once you're used to it,

157
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:26,800
you feel tight all over
if you miss a few days.

158
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:33,350
Wait.

159
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:35,830
You're a veterinarian.

160
00:08:37,190 --> 00:08:38,740
Did you use the same treatment on me

161
00:08:38,751 --> 00:08:39,697
that you use on donkeys?

162
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:42,160
It works anyway. What's the difference?

163
00:08:44,070 --> 00:08:45,510
It's been three days already.

164
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:47,430
He Dachui hasn't apologized,

165
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,830
and Zhu Jiru hasn't shown up.

166
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:52,160
Are we still rehearsing or what?

167
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:00,120
What exactly is going on?

168
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:02,390
Let me go find out.

169
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,390
Don't be desperate. Let them be.

170
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:12,040
But we're the ones stuck now.

171
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,360
You enjoyed hitting him,

172
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,600
but how do we fix this mess?

173
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:18,630
Fine, you find a better way then.

174
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:22,830
Tell He Dachui to break my leg.

175
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,870
An eye for an eye. How about that?

176
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:27,560
You big fool.

177
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:38,800
What are you trying to say?

178
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:42,120
Did you teach the kid the whole play

179
00:09:42,390 --> 00:09:43,390
or an opera excerpt?

180
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,070
An opera excerpt.

181
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,560
Call the kid over.

182
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:48,070
Cunren, Cunyi.

183
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:50,920
One of you plays Meng Liang,
and one plays Jiao Zan.

184
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,310
Work with the kid.

185
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,360
Let's perform the excerpt.

186
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:56,950
Call Zhu Jiru over to watch.

187
00:09:58,750 --> 00:09:59,590
Right.

188
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,430
Let's show those snobs,

189
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:04,560
that bunch of wimps.

190
00:10:04,950 --> 00:10:07,270
Let them open their eyes and see

191
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:09,720
if we have what it takes

192
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:13,030
and how we turn a kitchen maid

193
00:10:13,030 --> 00:10:14,720
into a young Wudan.

194
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,550
Someone's been killed!

195
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,240
Someone's been killed!

196
00:10:47,030 --> 00:10:49,510
The four of you

197
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,720
just rehearsed in secret

198
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:54,550
so quietly

199
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:56,960
right under my nose?

200
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,680
Tell me first.

201
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:00,913
How was the performance?

202
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:03,920
How was it?

203
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,440
Incredible.

204
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,120
Really incredible.

205
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,550
It's been 20 years,

206
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:18,030
and I've never been so impressed.

207
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:21,550
This girl's basics are solid,

208
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,200
her technique is authentic,

209
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:26,840
and her acting is brilliant.

210
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:30,790
How did the four of you do it?

211
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:34,240
You treated such a rare,

212
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,150
gifted talent like dirt.

213
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:41,270
If Gou Cunzhong hadn't found her,

214
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,870
her whole life

215
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,120
might have been wasted.

216
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:48,000
She started out as nothing.

217
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,080
Even her own uncle

218
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,360
noticed that she was

219
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,600
a sprout back then.

220
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,680
Qing'e,

221
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,150
do you still remember?

222
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:00,720
When Hu Sanyuan brought you
to my office,

223
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,720
you had a runny nose.

224
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,360
Hu Sanyuan said

225
00:12:04,630 --> 00:12:07,200
that as long as you had
some commodity grain,

226
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:10,040
you could be a guard or a cook

227
00:12:10,051 --> 00:12:11,080
or do whatever was needed.

228
00:12:11,550 --> 00:12:12,720
Who would have thought?

229
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:15,840
You've become such a talented Wudan.

230
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,870
It's truly impressive.

231
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:20,390
I'd even say that in a few years,

232
00:12:20,790 --> 00:12:21,630
if we're lucky,

233
00:12:22,030 --> 00:12:23,550
our livelihood

234
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,440
might just depend on her.

235
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:30,510
I called you here
to see this opera excerpt

236
00:12:30,510 --> 00:12:32,000
because I want to discuss something.

237
00:12:32,390 --> 00:12:35,550
Can we stop rehearsing
Bi Shang Liang Shan?

238
00:12:35,550 --> 00:12:37,080
Let's rehearse Yang Pai Feng first.

239
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:41,720
You've done the full Yang Pai Feng?

240
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,870
We've only done Da Jiao Zan so far.

241
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,110
But as you know,

242
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:48,600
this opera excerpt
is the core of the play.

243
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:50,600
Once we nail this,

244
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,150
the full-length play will be easy.

245
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,240
I'll go talk to Huang Zhengjing.

246
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:57,200
Let's push for Yang Pai Feng.

247
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,080
How sure are you?

248
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,870
If not, don't reveal the kid's talent.

249
00:13:02,870 --> 00:13:04,200
We don't want extra trouble

250
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:05,960
or anything bad for the kid.

251
00:13:06,510 --> 00:13:07,550
Put your mind at ease.

252
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:11,080
The kid was overlooked before

253
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,510
because we were blind.

254
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,910
If the kid is buried again now,

255
00:13:14,910 --> 00:13:16,360
we'll never forgive ourselves.

256
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:18,840
Qinqiang opera performers today

257
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,870
are already facing a talent gap.

258
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,870
Now, this kid has shown up.

259
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,600
On a smaller scale,

260
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,910
our troupe has a future.

261
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,870
On a bigger scale,

262
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,240
Qinqiang opera has a future.

263
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,870
Kid, do you hear that?

264
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,040
Who?

265
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:41,910
Hu Sanyuan's niece?

266
00:13:44,790 --> 00:13:48,030
We once treated her like nobody

267
00:13:48,030 --> 00:13:49,270
and sent her to the kitchen.

268
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:53,270
Who knew she'd be that tough?

269
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:55,320
Those veteran artists noticed

270
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,120
that she had real opera talent.

271
00:13:57,630 --> 00:14:00,360
They taught her while she stoked fires.

272
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:02,670
And those veteran artists

273
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:04,630
used traditional opera standards

274
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:05,910
to train the kid.

275
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:08,510
Her basic skills are rock solid.

276
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:11,080
Our trainees can't compare.

277
00:14:11,630 --> 00:14:13,320
Even those big stars in the troupe

278
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:14,360
are not as good as her.

279
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,720
You're being ridiculous.

280
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,960
How am I being ridiculous?

281
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:18,840
My dear Troupe Leader!

282
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:21,270
Our troupe is struggling right now.

283
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:24,120
We should put aside all our prejudices

284
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,270
and focus on the big picture.

285
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,510
I have no prejudice against anyone.

286
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:30,360
If you hadn't mentioned her,

287
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:31,550
I would've forgotten her.

288
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:33,000
That kid is a treasure.

289
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:36,030
We absolutely can't let her

290
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:37,550
go to waste in our hands again.

291
00:14:39,870 --> 00:14:41,200
Go to waste in our hands again?

292
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:45,750
What do you mean by that?

293
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:49,910
If I remember correctly,

294
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:52,240
Hu Sanyuan got that kid in

295
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,910
by messing around, right?

296
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:56,510
She slacked off here for a year

297
00:14:56,510 --> 00:14:57,750
and failed the exam.

298
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,390
According to the troupe's rules,

299
00:14:59,390 --> 00:15:00,750
she was supposed to be sent home.

300
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:03,910
I was the one who took pity on her

301
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,120
and let her tend the fire
in the kitchen.

302
00:15:06,550 --> 00:15:08,390
At least she'd get commodity grain.

303
00:15:08,390 --> 00:15:10,200
Why can't she act in Yang Pai Feng?

304
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,200
You do the job your post calls for.

305
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,870
I'm the troupe's leader.

306
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:16,150
How can I boss around the supply

307
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,163
and marketing cooperative?

308
00:15:17,630 --> 00:15:19,440
It's simple. How do you not get it?

309
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,910
How is this not our troupe's business?

310
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:25,150
Back then, you took that child

311
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:27,550
from the trainee class to tend fires.

312
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:29,670
So, why can't you take her now

313
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:31,150
from the kitchen back to training...

314
00:15:31,150 --> 00:15:32,030
Deputy Director Zhu!

315
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,440
Watch your tone.

316
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,600
Think about the big picture.

317
00:15:38,150 --> 00:15:40,790
It's fine if the show isn't a success.

318
00:15:40,790 --> 00:15:41,910
If it is,

319
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:42,960
do you know what it means?

320
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:44,390
What?

321
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,750
It means telling the world

322
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:50,000
that the County Troupe

323
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,550
spent several years

324
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:53,200
training dozens of successors,

325
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,040
and they aren't

326
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,270
as good as an apprentice

327
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:58,000
trained overnight by veteran artists.

328
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,600
How will you explain that

329
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,870
to the organization, the masses,

330
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,670
and the kids in the trainee class?

331
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:19,030
Listen, Zhu.

332
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:22,390
We can't just focus

333
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:25,030
on these minor gains.

334
00:16:25,510 --> 00:16:27,440
It's not just about one or two plays.

335
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,910
We need to have a broader vision.

336
00:16:30,689 --> 00:16:31,569
With your perspective,

337
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:32,779
what's there to argue with me

338
00:16:32,790 --> 00:16:34,030
about the bigger picture?

339
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,510
Let me stress this again.

340
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:40,150
Our reviving traditional opera

341
00:16:40,150 --> 00:16:42,000
isn't about reviving an old-style troupe

342
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,600
or some rotten old hierarchy.

343
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,200
This is about the bigger picture.

344
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:47,960
It's called having a vision.

345
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:57,200
Stop waiting.

346
00:16:57,910 --> 00:17:00,080
Zhu Jiru isn't coming.

347
00:17:01,790 --> 00:17:04,840
He should at least give us an answer.

348
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,550
Like a bun tossed to a dog,

349
00:17:06,550 --> 00:17:09,000
it's gone for good.
Isn't that his answer?

350
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:12,240
He got hotheaded last night,

351
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:15,750
talking about the future

352
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:18,790
of the troupe and Qinqiang opera.

353
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:21,030
He shouted those slogans.

354
00:17:21,030 --> 00:17:22,263
How could he show his face now?

355
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:25,960
That wimp is hiding again.

356
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:31,240
Can't we work around Zhu Jiru
and Huang Zhengjing?

357
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:28,590
Who?

358
00:18:30,550 --> 00:18:31,600
Here they come.

359
00:18:36,670 --> 00:18:37,510
What do you want?

360
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:38,910
A group fight?

361
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:40,910
Let's talk inside.

362
00:18:41,110 --> 00:18:42,720
Talk? Not with you.

363
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:45,280
You...

364
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,160
Don't hit guests who come with gifts.

365
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:50,320
Dachui,

366
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:52,240
we four old-timers

367
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,680
came to apologize today.

368
00:18:55,110 --> 00:18:56,640
I was wrong that day.

369
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,880
I shouldn't have talked nonsense.

370
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:00,030
In front of all those people,

371
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:01,790
I embarrassed you.

372
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:05,680
We're here to sincerely apologize.

373
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:07,030
Bro, here. Take it.

374
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:09,310
I don't need your apology.

375
00:19:10,030 --> 00:19:11,030
Leave, now.

376
00:19:11,030 --> 00:19:13,240
I'm telling you. This isn't over.

377
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:14,510
Dachui.

378
00:19:14,510 --> 00:19:15,350
- Here.
- What for?

379
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:17,000
Take it. Just take it.

380
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,480
Come on. Hit me.

381
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:20,240
Hit me as much as you want

382
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,270
until you feel better.

383
00:19:21,270 --> 00:19:23,480
Then we can move on, okay?

384
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,920
Knock it off.

385
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,030
Don't give me that routine.

386
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,560
Dachui,

387
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:30,830
the four of us together

388
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:32,880
are over 250,

389
00:19:33,590 --> 00:19:35,920
even older than Lian Po
when he apologized.

390
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:37,880
Let's just drop it.

391
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:40,550
We've lived together for decades.

392
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:42,200
We saw you grow from a little kid.

393
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,680
You saw us grow old too.

394
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:46,350
Conflicts are bound to happen.

395
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:49,160
Even teeth bite the tongue.

396
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:50,790
If we don't let this go,

397
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:53,070
we'll end up suffering.

398
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,320
Dachui,

399
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:56,720
isn't that right?

400
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:04,200
Aunt, you head back first.

401
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,790
I'll finish the rest of the work.

402
00:20:05,790 --> 00:20:06,630
Okay.

403
00:20:06,630 --> 00:20:07,480
Alright.

404
00:20:07,490 --> 00:20:09,110
I'm almost done.

405
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:17,280
Master Song.

406
00:20:17,430 --> 00:20:18,310
Master Song, sit here.

407
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:19,223
I'll massage your back.

408
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:20,350
No need, no need.

409
00:20:20,830 --> 00:20:23,160
I'll just go lie down and stretch out.

410
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,160
I banked the fire.

411
00:20:26,110 --> 00:20:27,550
Plump, I'm taking off.

412
00:20:28,070 --> 00:20:28,910
Okay.

413
00:20:29,070 --> 00:20:30,680
Don't forget to turn off the lights.

414
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:33,350
- Go to bed early.
- Okay.

415
00:20:33,350 --> 00:20:34,190
Goodbye.

416
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,030
Wait, wait a minute.

417
00:20:41,310 --> 00:20:42,310
I'm not done peeing!

418
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,070
You always do this.

419
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,320
No need.

420
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:50,880
Oh, come on!

421
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:52,310
Saluting Comrade Lei Feng!

422
00:20:52,310 --> 00:20:53,160
Cut the nonsense!

423
00:20:53,350 --> 00:20:54,190
Yes.

424
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:58,510
This pig has grown so fat.

425
00:20:58,510 --> 00:20:59,350
Yi Qing'e,

426
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:01,270
when are we going to kill and eat it?

427
00:21:01,270 --> 00:21:02,440
None of your business. Move.

428
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:03,300
Let go!

429
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:04,390
- Move.
- Let go!

430
00:21:04,510 --> 00:21:05,350
Let go!

431
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:07,070
So much nonsense. Move.

432
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:07,910
You...

433
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,000
Let's go.

434
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,320
Hurry up.

435
00:21:19,310 --> 00:21:21,270
Zhou Yuzhi, I love you!

436
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,480
Chu Jiahe, I love you!

437
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:33,310
Chu Jiahe! Chu Jiahe!

438
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,350
What a rare guest.

439
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,510
I'm looking for Chu Jiahe.

440
00:21:55,510 --> 00:21:56,680
Come in, it's cold out there.

441
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:58,320
Jiahe!

442
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,310
Chu Jiahe!

443
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:02,240
Chu Jiahe!

444
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:03,960
She's here for you.

445
00:22:04,270 --> 00:22:05,183
She's looking for you.

446
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:07,590
Chu Jiahe, come out for a second.

447
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:09,160
I need to talk to you.

448
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,830
Quiet down!

449
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:14,200
What did you say?

450
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,680
You're whispering like a fly.

451
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:19,270
Come out. I need to talk to you.

452
00:22:19,270 --> 00:22:21,240
No, just say it here.

453
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:28,720
I want to buy some clothes,

454
00:22:29,030 --> 00:22:30,240
but I don't know what to get.

455
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:32,830
You always look so good.

456
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,590
Where do you buy your clothes?

457
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,510
Can you go to the Department Store

458
00:22:39,510 --> 00:22:41,030
and buy some clothes with me?

459
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,680
Helping you?

460
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:44,070
I don't have time for that.

461
00:22:44,550 --> 00:22:45,480
Besides, my clothes

462
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:47,293
are from Shanghai
and the provincial capital.

463
00:22:47,590 --> 00:22:49,200
- Mine too!
- Mine too!

464
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:51,550
What nice clothes could they have here?

465
00:22:51,550 --> 00:22:52,590
- So tacky!
- Exactly!

466
00:22:52,590 --> 00:22:54,350
Only bumpkins buy clothes here.

467
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:55,190
Besides,

468
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:57,720
you just feed pigs and cook.

469
00:22:57,720 --> 00:22:58,846
Why do you need nice clothes?

470
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:01,590
Yeah, pigs don't look at you.

471
00:23:03,510 --> 00:23:04,480
Pigs don't care.

472
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,880
Come on, let's continue.

473
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:08,720
Keep going.

474
00:23:11,270 --> 00:23:15,440
Chu Jiahe! Chu Jiahe!

475
00:23:15,790 --> 00:23:20,200
Zhou Yuzhi! Zhou Yuzhi!

476
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:24,440
Chu Jiahe!

477
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:25,550
Chu Jiahe!

478
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,610
Chu Jiahe, one more!

479
00:23:27,620 --> 00:23:28,460
Chu Jiahe!

480
00:23:28,470 --> 00:23:29,640
Chu Jiahe, I love you!

481
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:30,550
I love you all too!

482
00:23:30,550 --> 00:23:31,390
I love you!

483
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,000
One more!

484
00:23:42,070 --> 00:23:44,000
One more! One more!

485
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,310
Chu Jiahe, I love you!

486
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:46,920
Chu Jiahe!

487
00:24:05,030 --> 00:24:05,870
Qing'e.

488
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:10,720
What's up?

489
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,100
You're not learning opera

490
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:18,930
with those four old guys today?

491
00:24:19,030 --> 00:24:20,440
They're busy.

492
00:24:20,550 --> 00:24:21,960
Busy picking on people.

493
00:24:22,350 --> 00:24:23,190
I know.

494
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:25,640
They went begging He Dachui.

495
00:24:26,270 --> 00:24:28,550
Gifts, apologies, the whole act.

496
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:29,960
Snot and tears were everywhere.

497
00:24:30,270 --> 00:24:31,590
They were a total mess.

498
00:24:31,590 --> 00:24:32,960
He Dachui was kind enough

499
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:34,550
to agree to drum for them.

500
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,350
Isn't this room cold?

501
00:24:39,180 --> 00:24:40,030
No, it isn't.

502
00:24:40,030 --> 00:24:41,070
Feel the draft down here.

503
00:24:41,070 --> 00:24:42,000
It's blowing through.

504
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,070
How could it not be cold?

505
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:45,240
I've been

506
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:46,720
a poor master.

507
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:48,240
I never came to see you

508
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,320
or looked after you.

509
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,110
Do you have mice here?

510
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,340
I'm not scared.

511
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,440
Well, I'm not a mouse.

512
00:24:53,510 --> 00:24:55,070
So, why are you scared of me?

513
00:24:55,510 --> 00:24:57,160
Look at this pad. It must be cold.

514
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,000
It's so thin.

515
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:59,640
I'll get an electric blanket.

516
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:01,200
Once plugged in, it'll be warm.

517
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:02,380
Is this quilt thick enough?

518
00:25:02,390 --> 00:25:03,250
Yes.

519
00:25:03,270 --> 00:25:04,130
Nonsense.

520
00:25:04,130 --> 00:25:05,310
I can't even reach you.

521
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:07,000
Why are you standing so far away?

522
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,240
Come over and sit for a while.

523
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:09,880
Chat with me for a bit.

524
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,790
You're not treating me as your master.

525
00:25:11,790 --> 00:25:13,640
Why are you being so distant?

526
00:25:13,830 --> 00:25:16,000
I still have that rock candy
for you. Here.

527
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:18,240
Have some rock candy. Take it.

528
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,200
I don't want it.

529
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,040
Take it.

530
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:21,590
Come here.

531
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:22,760
- Come here.
- No.

532
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:24,030
You said you're not cold.

533
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:25,440
Your little hands are freezing.

534
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,480
Let me warm them for you.

535
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,890
- I'm not cold.
- No need.

536
00:25:27,890 --> 00:25:29,170
- Let me warm you up.
- No need.

537
00:25:29,510 --> 00:25:30,350
Let me warm you up.

538
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:31,280
Come on.

539
00:25:31,550 --> 00:25:33,440
I just want to warm you up.

540
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:36,480
If only the dorm had a restroom.

541
00:25:36,480 --> 00:25:38,880
It's freezing this winter.

542
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:40,200
Don't move. Don't move.

543
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,270
Master Song!

544
00:25:41,270 --> 00:25:43,680
Don't yell.

545
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,480
Master Song! Master Song!

546
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:47,750
Don't yell.

547
00:25:47,750 --> 00:25:49,160
I just wanted to warm up.

548
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:51,160
You're young. Just warming up.

549
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,110
What's going on?

550
00:25:52,410 --> 00:25:53,270
I don't know.

551
00:25:53,270 --> 00:25:54,510
- Master Song.
- Don't yell.

552
00:25:56,310 --> 00:25:57,200
Master Song.

553
00:25:57,550 --> 00:25:58,590
Don't yell. Don't yell.

554
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:00,680
That wimp.

555
00:26:01,090 --> 00:26:02,000
Don't yell. Don't yell.

556
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,400
Just warming you up.

557
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:05,480
You wimp.

558
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:06,680
What are you doing?

559
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:07,520
Stop it!

560
00:26:09,110 --> 00:26:10,110
She's just a kid.

561
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:11,110
How could you touch her?

562
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,113
Have you no conscience?

563
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:14,480
I didn't do anything!

564
00:26:15,070 --> 00:26:16,000
What did he do to you?

565
00:26:17,030 --> 00:26:18,510
He tried

566
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:19,550
to untie my belt.

567
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:22,160
No, she tied a dead knot.

568
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,640
I couldn't get it open.

569
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:25,240
Let's go to the police.

570
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:27,240
Master Song, please!

571
00:26:27,310 --> 00:26:29,070
I'm a scumbag. I beg you!

572
00:26:29,110 --> 00:26:30,813
I lost my mind!

573
00:26:30,824 --> 00:26:31,779
In the dead of winter...

574
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:33,310
I'll hit myself. I'll do it!

575
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:34,670
Shut up.

576
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:39,280
You have two choices.

577
00:26:39,790 --> 00:26:40,960
The Public Security Bureau.

578
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:42,200
Go to prison.

579
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,270
Or just get out.

580
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:45,720
The farther, the better.

581
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,200
Never let the kid see you again.

582
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:48,040
Say something.

583
00:26:48,622 --> 00:26:50,499
I'll be the sous-chef.
You'll be the head chef.

584
00:26:50,510 --> 00:26:52,070
I'm begging you.

585
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:53,920
You whim.

586
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:01,200
What's wrong with him?

587
00:27:13,070 --> 00:27:14,440
Kid, don't be scared.

588
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:16,000
Try to steady yourself.

589
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:17,790
Listen to me, okay?

590
00:27:18,110 --> 00:27:19,350
If we report him to the police,

591
00:27:19,902 --> 00:27:21,042
he'll get eight or ten years

592
00:27:21,053 --> 00:27:22,550
for trying to assault you,

593
00:27:22,550 --> 00:27:23,920
yet even death wouldn't be enough.

594
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,270
But if we report it,

595
00:27:25,270 --> 00:27:27,030
the police will investigate

596
00:27:27,030 --> 00:27:27,880
and question everyone.

597
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:30,030
Then the whole troupe will know.

598
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,070
Once rumors like this start spreading,

599
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,640
who knows how they'll end up?

600
00:27:34,070 --> 00:27:35,640
His miserable life is worthless,

601
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:37,070
but you're still young.

602
00:27:37,510 --> 00:27:39,550
Your reputation
for the rest of your life...

603
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:41,320
Oh, kid.

604
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,000
What should we do?

605
00:27:45,270 --> 00:27:47,070
I want to go home.

606
00:27:47,070 --> 00:27:48,680
You can't go back now.

607
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:51,550
All your efforts will be for nothing.

608
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:53,790
All those years of suffering

609
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,480
would be completely wasted.

610
00:27:58,550 --> 00:27:59,510
Be good, okay?

611
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:07,240
Listen to me. Don't go back.

612
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,510
Stay calm on your own.

613
00:28:11,510 --> 00:28:12,440
Think about it.

614
00:28:13,030 --> 00:28:13,870
All right?

615
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,640
Master Liao, what are you doing?

616
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:09,433
Master Song! Master Song!

617
00:30:10,030 --> 00:30:12,350
Why did Master Liao
jump the wall and leave?

618
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,720
At least he has some shame.

619
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:18,520
What happened?

620
00:30:19,550 --> 00:30:20,590
Why bother with that?

621
00:30:20,590 --> 00:30:21,880
Let him go wherever he wants.

622
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:22,766
Just get back to work.

623
00:30:23,750 --> 00:30:25,030
It's fine, kid. Go to work.

624
00:30:25,550 --> 00:30:26,750
Keep at it. It's nothing.

625
00:30:56,590 --> 00:30:57,440
What's going on?

626
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,480
Why play different things?

627
00:30:58,480 --> 00:30:59,320
Captain,

628
00:31:00,030 --> 00:31:01,880
we haven't played for a long time.

629
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:02,793
We're all a bit rusty,

630
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:04,480
and the skill levels vary,

631
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:06,200
so I'm letting them practice alone.

632
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:07,310
Once they've improved,

633
00:31:07,310 --> 00:31:08,350
we'll rehearse together.

634
00:31:10,110 --> 00:31:10,950
Okay.

635
00:31:11,790 --> 00:31:13,960
What piece for the competition?

636
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:14,800
Have you decided yet?

637
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:17,070
I still want to do Zhan Shan Tong.

638
00:31:17,070 --> 00:31:18,460
- What?
- Zhan Shan Tong.

639
00:31:19,550 --> 00:31:20,390
Why?

640
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:21,680
I've thought about it.

641
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:23,480
This part is the most powerful.

642
00:31:23,880 --> 00:31:26,070
It captures the essence
of Qinqiang opera.

643
00:31:26,070 --> 00:31:27,070
What essence?

644
00:31:27,070 --> 00:31:28,183
It's desolate and resonant,

645
00:31:28,194 --> 00:31:29,367
accepting defeat but not fate.

646
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:32,310
But didn't you say the vocal style

647
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:34,270
is too hard even for professionals?

648
00:31:34,590 --> 00:31:36,640
Yes. I wanted to report that.

649
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:39,070
I plan to modify the arrangement.

650
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:43,110
We'll change the solo into a chorus.

651
00:31:43,703 --> 00:31:45,270
One line per person for the first half.

652
00:31:45,270 --> 00:31:47,240
Then, everyone joins in for the end.

653
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,790
I'd be thankful
if I could find one singer

654
00:31:49,790 --> 00:31:51,240
in this prison,

655
00:31:51,510 --> 00:31:53,400
and now you want a chorus?

656
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:55,880
A few lines are easy,

657
00:31:56,270 --> 00:31:58,240
but finishing the play
in one breath is hard.

658
00:31:58,510 --> 00:32:00,030
Didn't you run out of breath

659
00:32:00,030 --> 00:32:00,920
near the end that day?

660
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:05,240
Besides, singing Zhan Shan Tong alone

661
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:06,270
feels too bleak.

662
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:08,790
A chorus has real presence.

663
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:10,280
It hits harder too.

664
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:13,720
That works.

665
00:32:14,270 --> 00:32:16,270
I agree. Let's do Zhan Shan Tong.

666
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:19,110
And count me in for the chorus.

667
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:20,800
Captain,

668
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:23,310
we're called Rebirth Band.

669
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:25,270
You may not really fit.

670
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:35,400
♪From Hancheng County, Shaanxi♪

671
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:51,440
Is this hard to play?

672
00:33:53,070 --> 00:33:53,910
No.

673
00:33:58,030 --> 00:34:00,070
I watched you rehearse before.

674
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:01,920
It had so much energy.

675
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:04,790
It gave me goosebumps.

676
00:34:07,550 --> 00:34:09,010
Can you teach me to play this thing?

677
00:34:12,550 --> 00:34:13,390
Why?

678
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:16,340
Here's what I think.

679
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:18,750
Aren't you leaving in a year?

680
00:34:19,550 --> 00:34:22,030
Then, I'll take over your shift

681
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:24,160
and keep banging this thing.

682
00:34:31,860 --> 00:34:33,220
(Auditorium)

683
00:34:33,240 --> 00:34:34,080
Easy, easy.

684
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:35,040
Easy, easy.

685
00:34:35,070 --> 00:34:35,950
Good.

686
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:36,800
Good, good, good.

687
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:38,480
Right, good.

688
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,350
Yes, good.

689
00:34:39,350 --> 00:34:40,190
Good.

690
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:42,030
That branch. Yes, yes.

691
00:34:42,030 --> 00:34:42,870
That one, that one.

692
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:44,000
Fold them all.

693
00:34:45,110 --> 00:34:45,950
Right.

694
00:34:45,950 --> 00:34:47,160
(Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

695
00:34:47,160 --> 00:34:48,310
Fold it this way. Fold it.

696
00:34:48,310 --> 00:34:51,220
(Bi Shang Liang Shan
Lin Chong: Li Gang, Mrs. Lin: Mi Lan)

697
00:34:51,240 --> 00:34:52,080
A little more.

698
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:00,270
Coming through. Make way, please.

699
00:35:00,270 --> 00:35:01,310
Make way, please.

700
00:35:01,310 --> 00:35:02,640
Coming through.

701
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:04,440
Excuse me.

702
00:35:07,890 --> 00:35:08,880
Hurry up with the makeup.

703
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,070
We're running out of time.

704
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:51,110
Please, go easy on me.

705
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:53,000
During the rehearsal yesterday,

706
00:35:53,590 --> 00:35:55,280
it almost pinched my head off.

707
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:56,960
Thanks. Thank you.

708
00:36:21,220 --> 00:36:25,140
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe
Traditional Opera: Bi Shang Liang Shan)

709
00:36:29,590 --> 00:36:30,630
Too soon. Too soon.

710
00:36:33,630 --> 00:36:34,470
Come back.

711
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:38,640
What a wimp.

712
00:36:47,150 --> 00:36:47,990
What's this?

713
00:36:48,590 --> 00:36:49,430
Go.

714
00:37:06,710 --> 00:37:07,550
Laidi.

715
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:09,360
Come here. Give me a hand.

716
00:37:12,110 --> 00:37:13,510
Loosen my headpiece.

717
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:15,086
Mr. Gou got it way too tight.

718
00:37:15,097 --> 00:37:16,230
I haven't even gone on stage,

719
00:37:16,230 --> 00:37:17,473
and I'm already fainting here.

720
00:37:19,590 --> 00:37:21,030
Hurry, help me loosen this.

721
00:37:27,670 --> 00:37:34,360
♪Endless words to say♪

722
00:37:41,190 --> 00:37:50,150
♪In blood and tears,
the couple can't bear to part♪

723
00:37:50,150 --> 00:37:51,920
This actress is named Mi Lan.

724
00:37:52,550 --> 00:37:54,190
She's our star performer.

725
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,150
She is impressive.

726
00:38:03,150 --> 00:38:04,230
Honey.

727
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:07,030
Dear.

728
00:38:07,030 --> 00:38:08,400
Honey.

729
00:38:21,690 --> 00:38:22,550
Is this prearranged?

730
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:23,390
Go away.

731
00:39:05,510 --> 00:39:06,550
Since no one is speaking,

732
00:39:08,150 --> 00:39:09,190
I'll say a few words.

733
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:15,800
Since I started leading the troupe,

734
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,590
within the troupe,

735
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:20,190
and behind my back,

736
00:39:21,710 --> 00:39:23,230
there's been a certain rumor,

737
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:26,590
saying I don't know anything,

738
00:39:27,590 --> 00:39:29,510
and it's amateurs leading professionals,

739
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:32,110
disregarding artistic creation,

740
00:39:32,630 --> 00:39:34,070
and suppressing artists.

741
00:39:35,190 --> 00:39:36,800
Some people even went so far

742
00:39:37,670 --> 00:39:39,760
as to write joint letters

743
00:39:40,550 --> 00:39:42,510
to the higher-ups,

744
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:45,880
claiming the troupe's stagnation

745
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:47,960
was due to my incompetence

746
00:39:48,590 --> 00:39:50,840
and dictatorial ways.

747
00:39:51,550 --> 00:39:52,760
It got to the point

748
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:54,230
where I began to doubt myself,

749
00:39:55,110 --> 00:39:56,670
wondering if I was really incompetent.

750
00:39:57,630 --> 00:39:58,470
So,

751
00:39:59,550 --> 00:40:01,710
with the production
of Bi Shang Liang Shan,

752
00:40:02,710 --> 00:40:05,110
I delegated all my authority

753
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:08,760
to let professionals lead the way.

754
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:11,110
I stayed out of the creative process.

755
00:40:11,550 --> 00:40:12,550
Deputy Troupe Leader,

756
00:40:15,190 --> 00:40:16,230
I kept my word, right?

757
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:19,950
Yes.

758
00:40:21,760 --> 00:40:22,633
How did that turn out?

759
00:40:27,630 --> 00:40:28,470
Troupe Leader,

760
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:30,030
the premiere failed.

761
00:40:30,417 --> 00:40:31,477
I take full responsibility.

762
00:40:39,230 --> 00:40:40,760
You can't carry that blame.

763
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:43,710
I'm the troupe leader.

764
00:40:44,190 --> 00:40:45,960
The higher-ups will come after me.

765
00:40:48,360 --> 00:40:49,440
Let's be honest.

766
00:40:50,150 --> 00:40:53,760
Back when I was an amateur
leading the troupe,

767
00:40:54,230 --> 00:40:56,320
we never let a show get this bad.

768
00:41:03,070 --> 00:41:03,910
Here's the thing.

769
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:08,150
I'm the chief director of this show.

770
00:41:08,670 --> 00:41:10,230
For it to end up like this,

771
00:41:10,710 --> 00:41:11,710
I'm to blame.

772
00:41:14,710 --> 00:41:15,710
I wasn't

773
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:17,440
capable enough.

774
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:19,360
I'm sorry, everyone.

775
00:41:22,070 --> 00:41:22,960
Be quiet.

776
00:41:23,710 --> 00:41:25,190
This is a troupe meeting.

777
00:41:25,190 --> 00:41:26,360
Who are you to speak here?

778
00:41:26,710 --> 00:41:27,550
How dare you!

779
00:41:27,793 --> 00:41:29,452
Is that how you talk
to a veteran artist?

780
00:41:29,590 --> 00:41:30,843
Who let you get away with that?

781
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:36,030
Director Gu,

782
00:41:42,070 --> 00:41:43,510
I should thank you.

783
00:41:44,190 --> 00:41:46,110
You helped me get my confidence back.

784
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:50,400
I won't say anything else.

785
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:53,710
We all gave it our best.

786
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,440
Thank you, everyone.

787
00:42:00,030 --> 00:42:00,880
That's all.

788
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:04,680
Troupe Leader.

789
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:06,600
Troupe Leader.

790
00:42:08,070 --> 00:42:09,216
Troupe Leader, Troupe Leader.

791
00:42:20,230 --> 00:42:22,440
Huang Zhengjing is so ruthless.

792
00:42:29,590 --> 00:42:31,600
He cuts deep without one dirty word.

793
00:42:33,590 --> 00:42:34,590
I can't stay anymore.

794
00:42:36,150 --> 00:42:37,150
I really can't stay

795
00:42:38,460 --> 00:42:39,360
here anymore.

796
00:42:41,970 --> 00:42:42,960
I'm leaving.

797
00:42:43,540 --> 00:42:45,360
If you go, I'm going with you.

798
00:42:46,010 --> 00:42:48,070
I'm done with this crappy troupe.

799
00:42:48,210 --> 00:42:49,070
It's so humiliating.

800
00:42:49,070 --> 00:42:49,920
Yeah.

801
00:42:50,150 --> 00:42:52,320
We can make a living anywhere.

802
00:42:52,670 --> 00:42:53,510
You're leaving?

803
00:42:56,030 --> 00:42:57,230
You shouldn't have come back.

804
00:42:57,880 --> 00:42:59,030
Just leave, then.

805
00:42:59,510 --> 00:43:00,400
Leave right now.

806
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:03,760
All three of you can leave together.

807
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

808
00:43:09,320 --> 00:43:12,670
All the other prison propaganda teams
get a reward,

809
00:43:12,670 --> 00:43:13,630
except us.

810
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:14,880
Why is that?

811
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,110
Your plays aren't good.

812
00:43:17,110 --> 00:43:19,630
You have such great veteran artists.

813
00:43:19,630 --> 00:43:20,840
Why don't you use them?

814
00:43:20,840 --> 00:43:21,680
Da Jiao Zan.

815
00:43:21,680 --> 00:43:23,440
An old play. No one can perform it.

816
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:26,070
Such great skills. A fine Wudan.

817
00:43:26,070 --> 00:43:27,070
Yi Qing'e,

818
00:43:27,070 --> 00:43:28,230
take the lead role.

819
00:43:28,230 --> 00:43:29,280
I'm nervous.

820
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:31,800
Go!

821
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

822
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

823
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

824
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

825
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

826
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

827
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

828
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

829
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

830
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

831
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

832
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

833
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

834
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

835
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

836
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

837
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

838
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

839
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

840
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

841
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

